     Occupational Therapy Faculty Practice  Providing occupation-focused, evidence-based and client-centered occupational therapy services to children, youth, adults and families  The UIC Occupational Therapy (OT) Faculty Practice applies the UIC Department of Occupational Therapy’s community-engaged Scholarship of Practice Model, which emphasizes the meaningful relationships between community partnerships, research evidence and occupational therapy practice, in its evaluation, intervention and consultation services.      Our services           Children, youth and families (CYF)   For children and youth so that they may participate in the occupations that are meaningful to them and their families.            Self-management   For adults experiencing chronic conditions so that they may participate in the occupations that are meaningful to them and their families.                 Come see us   Hours Monday-Friday: 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. Saturday-Sunday: Closed  (dependent on occupational therapist availability)    You can contact us at:     Fax  (312) 355-3588               Occupational Therapy    Back to main content           Admissions and Programs    Expand Admissions and Programs menu          MS in Occupational Therapy    Expand MS in Occupational Therapy menu          What to Expect    Expand What to Expect menu          Student Leadership      Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Expand After You Apply menu          Checklist for Admitted Students      FAQs    Fieldwork    Graduation and Credentialing      Doctor of Occupational Therapy    Expand Doctor of Occupational Therapy menu          What to Expect    Before You Apply    Applying    After You Apply    Faculty Advisors      Co-enrolling in the MS and OTD programs      Occupational Therapy Faculty Practice    Expand Occupational Therapy Faculty Practice menu          Children, Youth and Families    Self-Management      Research and Scholarship    News    Calendar    Directory    Contact           